<!DOCTYPE Test SYSTEM '../../../../../../../../../../../../../test.dtd'>
<Test
    ID="exec1011"
    date-of-creation="2005-6-30"
    timeout="1"
    >
        
        
        <APITestDescription>
            <TestedClass name="java.lang.Runtime"/>
            <TestedMethod name="public Process exec(String[] cmdarray)"/>
            <Description>
The test is against exec1011 method.
It exerecises the fillowing:

1) Executes the specified command and arguments in a separate process.

For testing purposes JVM is used;
the test access it using the "java.home" property.
The test performs the following checks on the method.
- If a String[] argument contains both the "java" and the "-help" tokens,
  that is, the command to launch JVM is correct,
  the exit value returned on a process exit is 0.
- If a String[] argument doesn't contain the "-help" token, 
  that is, the command to launch JVM is incorrect,
  the exit value returned on a process exit is 1.
            </Description>
            </APITestDescription>
        <Source name="exec1011.java"/>
        <Runner ID="Runtime">
            <Param name="toRun" value="org.apache.harmony.test.func.api.java.lang.Runtime.exec.exec10.exec1011.exec1011"/>
        </Runner>
        <Restriction name="OtherVMOnly"/>
</Test>
